TY  - JOUR
T1  - Fact and Fiction in Analyzing Research on Participative Decision Making: A Critique of Cotton, Vollrath, Froggatt, Lengnick-Hall, and Jennings
AU  - Leana, Carrie R.
AU  - Locke, Edwin A.
AU  - Schweiger, David M.
Y1  - 1990/01/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1990.4308286
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1990.4308286
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 137
EP  - 146
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A review by Cotton, Vollrath, Froggatt, Lengnick-Hall, and Jennings (1988) concluded that previously reported discrepancies in the results among studies of participative decision making (PDM) are largely due to differences in the form of PDM used. In this article we critique both the procedures used and the conclusions reached by these authors. Problems were found in how they classified, sampled, and interpreted the results of PDM studies. Suggestions for future research and interpretations of the PDM literature are also discussed.
AB  - A review by Cotton, Vollrath, Froggatt, Lengnick-Hall, and Jennings (1988) concluded that previously reported discrepancies in the results among studies of participative decision making (PDM) are largely due to differences in the form of PDM used. In this article we critique both the procedures used and the conclusions reached by these authors. Problems were found in how they classified, sampled, and interpreted the results of PDM studies. Suggestions for future research and interpretations of the PDM literature are also discussed.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1990.4308286
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1990.4308286
Y2  - 2026/04/24
ER  - 
